<p style="margin: 0px;">
Above all, we are about people. A philosophy of inclusion drives our organization every day and helps us win in a diverse, global marketplace.
</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px;"><b>Diversity Organizations</b></p>
<p style="margin: 0px;">
Our work environment draws on the strength of every associate to build an atmosphere of personal and professional growth. These Bank of America organizations help make diversity work:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>The Diversity Advisory Council: A group of associates who are recognized as leaders in their businesses and who can have an impact for change at the corporate level.</li>
	<li>The Diversity Business Councils: Councils that address inclusion issues across our businesses. These identify issues and recommend strategies to make their business group a place where all associates can do their best work.</li>
	<li>The Diversity network: One of five networks that make up Team Bank of America (link to http://www.bankofamerica.com/teambank/), the Diversity Network is comprised of geographically based volunteer teams of associates. The Network's mission is to encourage and capitalize on the diversity of our associates and promote personal and professional development. Membership is open to associates at all levels of the company.</li>
	<li>Affinity Groups: Bank of America recognizes several affinity groups, that is, groups of associates with a common interest and those who support them. Currently, there are groups organized for Asian Americans, Black and African Americans, people with disabilities, Hispanic/Latino associates, Lesbian/Gay/Bisexual/Transgender associates, parents, and women.</li>
</ul>

